weather.description: It's going to rain, though it may be more of a second-half issue. Winds remain light.
Looking like most of the rain holds just south, still a chance for in-game rain, especially later.
It's going to pour for most of the day in Seattle, might be breaking up and clearing some by Sunday evening, but still think it's at least off and on wet.

It's going to rain, likely all game long. Winds remain light. Worth noting that in both of these Mid-Atlantic games (WASH and BAL) the rain should be increasing through the game, so increasingly wet/slick late.
Can't rule out some showers, doesn't look like much.
